13 COMMITTEE SUBSTITUTE
14 An Act relating to motor vehicles; prohibiting
certain entities from providing certain
15 recommendations; providing certain cause of civil
action for certain violation; prohibiting certain
16 entities from withholding certain grants in certain
circumstance; providing certain cause of civil action
17 for certain violation; exempting certain driving
school; providing for codification; providing an
18 effective date; and declaring an emergency.
19
20
21 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
22 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
23 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 808.1 of Title 47, unless there
24 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
SB1595 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 A. 1. No agency, entity, or instrumentality of this state, or
2 entity contracted with such, shall provide specific recommendations
3 in favor of or against a commercial driver training school in this
4 state.
5 2. A violation of the provisions of paragraph 1 of this
6 subsection shall be a cause of civil action for the commercial
7 driver training school affected by such violation against the
8 violating agency, entity, or instrumentality, or entity contracted
9 with such.
10 B. 1. No agency, entity, or instrumentality of this state, or
11 entity contracted with such, that administers grants for students of
12 commercial driver training schools in this state shall withhold such
13 grants based on the student’s choice of a specific school.
14 2. A violation of the provisions of paragraph 1 of this
15 subsection shall be a cause of civil action for the commercial
16 driver training school or student affected by such violation against
17 the violating agency, entity, or instrumentality, or entity
18 contracted with such.
19 C. The provisions of this section shall not apply to any
20 commercial driver training school administered by the Oklahoma
21 Department of Corrections.
22 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
23 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
24 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
SB1595 HFLR Page 2
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 decl ared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
2 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
3
